# /etc/hosts template for the LAN cluster - REPLACE these IPs with your real ones
# (on each machine run: hostname -I). Paste the 4 lines below at the END of /etc/hosts
# on EVERY node, identical on all of them. After that, cluster/hosts refers to the
# nodes by name, so only this mapping changes when the LAN/IPs change.
192.168.1.11   node1
192.168.1.12   node2
192.168.1.13   node3
192.168.1.14   node4
